{{Quote|So strong, we thought&hellip; so wrong&hellip;|Ajunta Pall|<ref name="KOTOR" />}}
'''Ajunta Pall''' was a [[Gender/Legends|male]] [[Human/Legends|Human]] [[Jedi Master/Legends|Jedi Master]] and the leader of the [[Dark Jedi/Legends|Dark Jedi]] who were [[Exiles|exiled]] from the [[Jedi Order/Legends|Jedi Order]] and the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]] following the [[Hundred-Year Darkness/Legends|Hundred-Year Darkness]]. Upon his arrival on [[Korriban/Legends|Korriban]], he became the first [[Dark Lord of the Sith/Legends|Dark Lord of the Sith]]. He was regarded as the manifestation of [[Typhojem/Legends|Typhojem, the Left-Handed God]] by the [[Kissai]]. Long after his death, his spirit was redeemed by the [[Jedi Knight/Legends|Jedi Knight]] [[Revan/Legends|Revan]] during the [[Jedi Civil War]].

==Biography==
===In life===
{{Quote|Are you&hellip; Ajunta Pall?''"<br />"''I&hellip; had a name, once. Ajunta Pall. Yes, that was my name. I was one of many. We were servants of the dark side&hellip; Sith Lords, we called ourselves. So proud. In the end we were not so proud. We hid&hellip; hid from those we had betrayed. We fell&hellip; and I knew it would be so.|Revan and the spirit of Ajunta Pall|<ref name="KOTOR" />}}
[[File:ExiledDarkJedi-BoS.jpg|thumb|left|150px|Escorted by [[XoXaan]], Sorzus Syn, and [[Remulus Dreypa]], Pall arrives on Korriban.]]
A [[Force-sensitive/Legends|Force-sensitive]] [[Human/Legends|Human]], Ajunta Pall was a member of the [[Jedi Order/Legends|Jedi Order]] following the [[First Great Schism]]. Undergoing [[Jedi training/Legends|training]] in the ways of [[The Force/Legends|the Force]], Pall first attained the rank of [[Jedi Knight/Legends|Jedi Knight]], then attained the rank of [[Jedi Master/Legends|Jedi Master]] and began studying the ways of [[Sith alchemy/Legends|alchemy]]. Eventually through his studies, Master Pall discovered the secret of creating and shaping life; fearful of this power, the Order deemed it an abomination of the Force and sought to erase all practice of it. The [[Jedi High Council/Legends|Jedi High Council]] [[Second Great Schism|barred the teachings of Pall and his followers]], deeming him a pawn of the [[Dark side of the Force/Legends|dark side of the Force]].<ref name="Tomb of Ajunta Pall">{{TORcite|type=codex|Tomb of Ajunta Pall}}</ref>

Angered by what they deemed Jedi arrogance, Master Pall and his followers declared war on the Jedi Order, beginning a century-long conflict that would be known to history as the [[Hundred-Year Darkness/Legends|Hundred-Year Darkness]]. Obtaining significant power, the now High General Pall slew more than a dozen Jedi during the [[Battle of Corbos|final battle]] of the war on [[Corbos]], but despite this, he and his fellow [[Dark Jedi/Legends|Dark Jedi]] were still defeated. Captured by his former Jedi comrades, Master Pall and his followers were stripped of their ranks and their weapons, and exiled from space controlled by the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]].<ref name="JvS">[[Jedi vs. Sith: The Essential Guide to the Force (real-life book)|''Jedi vs. Sith: The Essential Guide to the Force'']]</ref>

[[File:Ziost_egtf.jpg|thumb|right|200px|Ajunta Pall, exiled on Ziost]]
Traveling from one planet to the other in search of a habitable world, the [[Exiles]] eventually discovered [[Korriban/Legends|Korriban]] on the [[Outer Rim Territories/Legends|Outer Rim]]. Venturing out into the wastes of the desert planet, the Exiles were intrigued upon discovering the world was home to a Force-sensitive species, known as the [[Sith (species)/Legends|Sith]], who, while relatively primitive when compared to the Dark Jedi, were quite creative in their knowledge of the Force. The Sith, under their King [[Hakagram Graush]], initially resisted the Dark Jedi's attempt to obtain their knowledge and subjugate them; however, Pall managed to recruit the King's [[Shadow Hand]] to their side, with the result that Graush was betrayed to the Dark Jedi, and Pall personally executed Graush with his own sword. Afterwards, the Sith species, in awe of Pall and his followers' ships and technology, as well as their skills in manipulating the Force, quickly came to worship the visitors to their planet, hailing them as their gods,<ref name="KOTORCG">''[[Knights of the Old Republic Campaign Guide]]''</ref><ref name="KOTOR" /><ref name="JvS" /> Pall himself believed to be the manifestation of the Left-Handed [[Deity/Legends|God]] [[Typhojem/Legends|Typhojem]] by their [[Kissai]] [[Priest/Legends|priest]] caste. Pall and his followers then subjugated the natives, and his new Sith subjects revered him as their "[[Jen'ari]]," meaning "Dark Lord," a position coveted by fellow Exile [[Sorzus Syn]]. However, Pall was too cautious to claim the title of ''[[Sith'ari/Legends|Sith'ari]]'', a prophesied overlord of the Sith.<ref name="Book of Sith">''[[Book of Sith: Secrets from the Dark Side]]''</ref>

As the first [[Dark Lord of the Sith/Legends|Dark Lord of the Sith]], Ajunta Pall founded the [[Sith Empire/Legends|first Sith Empire]] and expanded it onto other worlds. Pall had a [[Sith Citadel (Ziost)|citadel]] built for himself to rule from on the planet [[Ziost/Legends|Ziost]].<ref name="Book of Sith" /> Pall eventually [[Death/Legends|died]] after serving the Empire for many decades, but his Empire lived on. His body was returned to Korriban, where it was placed in a massive [[Tomb of Ajunta Pall|tomb]] in what would come to be called the [[Valley of the Dark Lords/Legends|Valley of the Dark Lords]].<ref name="JvS" />

===In death===
{{Quote|If&hellip; if I could return. Oh, my Master&hellip; it has been&hellip; so long&hellip; and I regret so much&hellip;|Ajunta Pall, after Revan convinced him to turn back to the light|<ref name="KOTOR" />}}
After his physical death, Ajunta Pall's [[Force ghost/Legends|spirit]] persisted within his tomb, having attached his soul to the physical world through his extensive knowledge of alchemy. Over the centuries, he began to question his actions as a Sith Lord and the downfall the Lords experienced at each other's hand.<ref name="KOTOR" /> According to legend, the [[Jedi Council/Legends|Jedi Council]] took possession of [[Ajunta Pall's lightsaber]] after his death and stored it inside the Great Jedi Library.<ref name="FDCR">''[[Star Wars: Force and Destiny Core Rulebook]]''</ref>

{{GameLS}}
[[File:Ajuntaspirit.jpg|200px|thumb|left|Ajunta Pall's spirit after his physical death]]
Millennia after his death, during the [[Jedi Civil War]], Jedi Knight [[Revan/Legends|Revan]] entered Ajunta Pall's tomb to retrieve the Sith Lord's [[Sword of Ajunta Pall|sword]] so that he could gain prestige from the nearby [[Sith Academy (Korriban)|Sith academy]], which he hoped would ultimately lead to his accessing a [[Star Map]] containing partial coordinates of the [[Star Forge]]. Ajunta Pall appeared as a spirit and told Revan of his actions as a Sith, with disappointment and shame, telling him of how the Jedi were not what drove the Sith to destruction after the Hundred-Year Darkness. Pall explained how the Sith themselves battled each other and led their Order close to death and that he felt nothing but remorse. Revan removed the Dark Lord's blade and convinced Pall to turn away from the dark side and return to the [[Light side of the Force/Legends|light]]. After Revan took the blade, Pall advised him not to keep it, saying it was the blade that killed him. Letting go of his pain and anguish, Pall returned to the light and became one with the Force, finding peace at last. Revan then gave the sword to [[Sith Master/Legends|Master]] [[Uthar Wynn]] at the academy, obtaining the prestige necessary to reach the Star Map.<ref name="KOTOR" />
{{Endgame}}

Before his spirit was finished, Pall hinted at a secret source of Sith power. He was unable to reconcile conflicted images of whether Revan had discovered this source of power, or would soon do so.<ref name="KOTOR" />

==Behind the scenes==
[[File:Ajuntastat.jpg|thumb|right|130px|A possible statue of Ajunta Pall]]
Ajunta Pall's tomb is one of the side quests available in the Korriban segment of the video game ''[[Star Wars: Knights of the Old Republic]]''. In the game, he recognizes the player character's true identity. The main character can either help him become one with the Force (for "light-side points"), fight him and destroy his spirit (for "dark-side points"), or fail to take him to the light and let his spirit fade away. The player may also choose to keep the sword instead of giving it to Uthar.

In the game ''Star Wars: Knights of the Old Republic'', Ajunta Pall's spirit appears as a generic human Dark Jedi with an energy shield activated to simulate transparency.

The statue of Ajunta Pall seen in his tomb is identical to one seen in the destroyed [[Jedi Enclave]] on [[Dantooine/Legends|Dantooine]] in [[Star Wars: Knights of the Old Republic II: The Sith Lords|''Knights of the Old Republic II'']].

Originally, Pall's tomb was supposed to be that of [[Freedon Nadd]], who actually had been buried on [[Dxun/Legends|Dxun]]. The error was corrected with the introduction of Pall into the scenario; however, it is still present in the game files as Pall is referred to as Nadd in the dialogue *.dlg files and character *.utc file.

Though Ajunta Pall would have been well over 100 years old by the end of the Hundred-Year Darkness, the artwork of him in [[Jedi vs. Sith: The Essential Guide to the Force (real-life book)|Jedi vs. Sith: The Essential Guide to the Force]] depicted him as looking much younger.

